originalText.text: So wow!!! Was looking for a less crowded laundromat on a late Sunday and this came up on Google. Um... If you want your clothes coming out smelling with mildew then come here to wash your clothes. At $3.00 a load for the small washer I expect a little better wash then I got. The dryers are. 25 for 6 minutes but when I tried to stop the dryer and take out my shirts, it just kept spinning around and around. So the machines are dirty, oh and half of them have out of order signs. Never seen so many signs. They get one star for not being crowded on a Sunday afternoon. Now I know why.

originalText.text: I'm not sure why I did not receive the same treatment as previous reviewers, but I recently moved into the neighborhood and upon my first visit (which is sure to be my last) I felt nothing but a hostile atmosphere in the air, which was provided by a man I assume was the owner. Between no spoken dialogue and more than a handful of very nasty glares, I felt as if I was doing something wrong simply by having a physical presence in his store. Laundry sucks enough, this isn't the environment you want to add on top. Regardless of if it is clean and slightly less expensive than other ones in the area, I'll happily pay the difference. Definitely NOT recommended.

originalText.text: Hi guys! Let me tell you what just happened to me. I went to this laundromat to ask how much they charge perLB and also to inform them that a dog had used the bathroom in front of his store.  don’t you know he does act like he didn’t work there and then another customer came in waiting so he took the customer and he looked at me and he said there’s no bathroom no bathroom and I looked at him and I said I don’t even come here for a restroom.  He rolledhis eyes  and walked away for me..... I never experienced anything like that in my life!

originalText.text: If I could give this place zero stars I would. Set an alarm to come back and get my stuff. Came in 1 minute after and the employee had already taken my stuff out of the dryer and threw it in a cart. Maybe you wouldn’t run out of washers and dryers if 60% of them didn’t have an out of order sign. Absolutely awful. The employees are rude as well.
